cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MED, cs.CL

This paper deals with the classification of abnormalities in chest X-ray images using deep learning techniques. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the use of multi-task learning, which involves training the model to perform multiple tasks simultaneously, such as segmentation of the lungs and heart. This suggests that the paper could also be classified under cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper deals with medical imaging, which could place it under cs.MED (Medical Informatics). Finally, the paper discusses the issue of label noise, which could suggest a classification under cs.CL (Computation and Language).
